def_en: If you describe a place as a labyrinth, you mean that it is made up of a complicated series of paths or passages, through which it is difficult to find your way.

def_cn: 错综复杂的事物；千头万绪的局面；盘根错节的情况
def_en: If you describe a situation, process, or area of knowledge as a labyrinth, you mean that it is very complicated.
